---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
    title="Realistic Land Siting Alternatives | TomorrowBeginsHere.com"
    description="Compare data center land use against realistic zoning alternatives like warehouse logistics hubs or dense residential subdivisions."
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 border-b border-tech-blue/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-950/80 via-slate-900/95 to-tech-blue/80 z-0 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/texas-data-centers-network.png')] bg-cover bg-center z-0 opacity-15 mix-blend-overlay"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 lg:py-24 text-center">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-indigo-500/20 text-indigo-300 font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-6 border border-indigo-500/30 backdrop-blur-sm">Pillar 04 • Land Siting Options</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight leading-tight">
                A Much Better<br><span class="text-indigo-300">Alternative</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-200 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-light">
                Commercially zoned land will be developed. The honest question is not whether to build, but what choice brings the best balance of tax base and public preservation.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white relative">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none">
                
                <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-800 font-semibold mb-8">
                    A lot of the worry I hear compares a data center to an empty green field. But that was never the real choice.
                </p>

                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    The honest comparison is what else gets built on that land. A warehouse complex with trucks in and out all day. A subdivision pulling on the same water and the same roads. Or nothing at all, generating nothing for the county.
                </p>

                <!-- Comparison Table -->
                <div class="my-12 overflow-x-auto border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl shadow-sm">
                    <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse bg-white text-sm">
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-200">
                                <th class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Impact Category</th>
                                <th class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-900 bg-tech-blue/5 text-tech-blue">Modern Data Center</th>
                                <th class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Logistics Warehouse</th>
                                <th class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Residential Subdivision</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Daily Car/Truck Traffic</td>
                                <td class="p-4 bg-tech-blue/5 text-slate-700">**Minimal** (20-30 staff vehicles total)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Extreme** (500+ diesel trucks/day)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**High** (1,500+ commuter cars/day)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Local Noise & Light</td>
                                <td class="p-4 bg-tech-blue/5 text-slate-700">**Low** (Acoustic baffling, buffer setbacks)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**High** (Beeping trucks, loading docks, 24/7 bays)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Moderate** (Suburban ambient, streetlights)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Assessed Property Value</td>
                                <td class="p-4 bg-tech-blue/5 text-slate-700">**Highest** (Highly valued server hardware/substations)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Low-Moderate** (Basic metal framing & concrete slab)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Moderate** (Distributed among 1,000+ homes)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">School & Public Demand</td>
                                <td class="p-4 bg-tech-blue/5 text-slate-700">**Zero** (No school enrollment demand, private security)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Low** (No student demand, high public road wear)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Highest** (1,500+ children added to ISD, heavy park/road demands)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="p-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Water Consumption</td>
                                <td class="p-4 bg-tech-blue/5 text-slate-700">**Extremely Low** (Aqueous air cooling, closed-loop systems)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**Low** (Basic restrooms)</td>
                                <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">**High** (Irrigation, lawns, pools, household taps)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6 text-lg font-medium">
                    Next to those options, a data center is quiet, low-traffic, and pays far more in property tax for its footprint. Look at the real alternatives, not an imaginary one.
                </p>

                <hr class="border-slate-200 my-12">

                <div class="text-center bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    <p class="text-slate-500 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-bold">Explore the next pillar</p>
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Pillar 05: The Grid Story — On-Site Power & Balance</h4>
                    <a href="/texas-data-centers/grid-stabilizer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-tech-blue hover:bg-tech-blue/90 text-white font-bold rounded-xl transition-colors">
                        Next: Grid Stabilization
                        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
